# Ported from RequestsModuleTests.cs — NO TESTS PORTED.
#
# Every test in this C# file drives the module's request pipeline through the
# `internal` Requests.Send(...) entry point with a mocked HttpMessageHandler /
# HttpClient so it can inspect the outgoing HttpRequestMessage without touching the
# network. That mock infrastructure (HttpMessageHandler subclassing, HttpClient
# injection) has no surface in Sharpy, and Requests.Send is not callable from .spy,
# so none of these tests are reachable.
#
# Omitted tests and why:
#   - Get_ReturnsOkResultOnSuccess, Get_PublicEntryPointWorks,
#     Post_WithJsonBody_SendsJsonContentType, Post_WithFormData_*,
#     Post_JsonTakesPrecedenceOverData, CustomHeaders_AreForwardedOnRequest,
#     QueryParams_* (3), Timeout_TriggersTimeoutError,
#     ConnectionFailure_TriggersConnectionError, AllHttpMethods_DispatchCorrectly:
#       require internal Requests.Send + a mock HttpMessageHandler to capture the
#       request — not reachable / not hermetic.
#   - NullUrl_ReturnsErrRequestException: passes null! url to Send — internal API and
#     a null literal not expressible in type-safe Sharpy (Axiom 3).
#   - Get_PublicMethodInvokes: the one public-API test makes a real DNS/connection
#     attempt to an invalid host — requires network connectivity, not hermetic.
#
# Hermetic, reachable Session configuration tests live in
# requests_session_tests.spy.

import requests
